<h2 id="head-ff11f0da0a4cd245270f188d8a7299b4084d0328">Chatter</h2>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Hrmmm... Perhaps this page should be renamed to 'Effects from hacking <em><strong>and</strong></em> eating corpses'??? <p>
(part of the discussion moved to <a href="./Modules_2fZothiqband_2fCannibal">Modules/Zothiqband/Cannibal</a>) 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a></strong>: Minor idea... every bite snatched from a dungeon corpse could maybe provide a 1000 pt piety hit to worshippers of Eru, Manwe, Tulkas and Yavanna (though maybe only a 500 pt one for Yav, she believes more in the cycle-of-life bit... <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> ) 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./FeathinSilyar">FeathinSilyar</a></strong>:  1000 piety hit sounds a bit high...How about the level of the monster, multiplied by 5 if it is sentient? 
</p>
<hr>
 <p>
<strong><a href="./FeathinSilyar">FeathinSilyar</a></strong>:  I just hacked meats off of a Mature Black Dragon, and eating the hacked meats provided acid resistance.  Tried hacking then off of some uniques and their meats were inert.  Perhaps monster meats convey whatever the corpse does, and uniques don't?  Could probably be an unexpected result of some coding, or perhaps intended since many unique corpses have very powerful effects. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./FeathinSilyar">FeathinSilyar</a></strong>:  Eating hacked meat from Glaurung gives fire resistance, so it works for some uniques as well. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./RedNaga">RedNaga</a></strong>: Mmmm.... i hacked some meat from a fire hound and it gave me resist fire - i brought the remaining meat with me for a while and when i ate it again i *didn't* get resist fire! I seem to remember also that hacked meat does rot away after some time - i think the resistance goes away as well after some time, but much before the meat spoils - either that or a very nasty bug! <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
I think it should be worthy to mention here the dangers of <strong>hacking</strong> meat in first place! (i.e. mostly the possibility that hacking a breather will shower you with his breath element for an amount of damage that is related to the corpse weight, and can thus be *huge* even with low level monsters) 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./FeathinSilyar">FeathinSilyar</a></strong>:  Yeah, I crossed my fingers before hacking Glaurung, but I had fire immunity and some 1000 hp.  He hit with fire and then poison, and with poison resistance that did some 250 or so damage.  Generally, if you need the meat for a resistance, you'll die trying to get it.  I expect that Glaurung's meat gives poison resistance as well, but it wouldn't show since I have poison resistance already and there isn't a double stack for that like there is for fire resistance.  It probably makes it quite easy to not notice lots of resistances when eating meats. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./RedNaga">RedNaga</a></strong>: i don't think you can get greater resists from eating corpses, but you should get a message on temporary poison resist if you get it - at least you get it when you quaff a potion of resistance! Poison damage is reduced in the same way as other ones if you have double resistance. 
</p>
